      "topic": "cp invocation -a",
      "category": "filesystem",
      "fact_type": "option",
      "statement": "The `cp invocation` -a option Preserve as much as possible of the structure and attributes of the original files in the copy (but do not attempt to preserve internal directory structure; i.e., ‘ ls -U ’ may list the entries in a copied directory in a different order).",
      "conditions": [],
      "examples": [
        "cp invocation -a"
      ],
      "source": "cp invocation (GNU Coreutils 9.11)",
